body.plain: ‘Fool’s Gold’ is the lead single off of Sugar Mountain, the debut album from Holly Rankin, who performs under the persona ‘Jack River’.

annotations: Our stars came in a packet of two

In an interview with triple j for the ‘Inspired’ segment, Holly speaks about how the beginning of the song came about in New York. She ventured to the city on a writing trip, as she was feeling a lack of inspiration, and found her ‘Fool’s Gold’!

This lyric was the second that she thought up, taking inspiration from a packet containing two stars. This refers to her and her crush at the time, the one that does not like roller-coasters.

You don’t like rollercoasters
 How could you ever love a girl like me?

Through this line Jack River alludes to the fact that she is difficult to love by comparing herself to a ‘roller coaster’ telling the person who she has a crush on “How could you ever love a girl like me?”
